{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:39:36.938Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Identifying Preview Clients**\n\nI've got a list of preview clients: Apex Sovereign Group, Global Retail Enclave, and Sovereign Logistics Unit are all flagged. There's also `client-004` and `client-005` on the list.\n\n\n**Verifying Detail Navigation**\n\nI'm now checking the client details drawer in `app/admin/clients/page.tsx`. My current focus is verifying how it links to the deep details audit page (`/admin/clients/[id]`). Specifically, I'm examining the drawer's footer actions to see the navigation to the detailed audit page.\n\n\n**Adding Deep Audit Link**\n\nI've hit a snag. The client details drawer doesn't have a direct link to the deep audit page. Clicking a table row only opens the drawer, and I'm now thinking about adding a button within the drawer's header or footer that navigates to the detailed audit page, `/admin/clients/${selectedClient.id}`.\n\n\n**Designing Premium Client Page**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in designing the `/admin/clients/[id]/page.tsx` component. The vision is clear: a \"holographic diagnostic panel\" that presents a strategic, scientific, and custom audit of a single sovereign client enclave tenant. I'm focusing on the first 5 seconds of user interaction, aiming to present client identity, region, security posture, live sandbox status, operational telemetry, and active HSM key integrity. I'm also planning the interactive elements, including tabbed sections, hover states, dynamic indicators, and mock console logs, and seeing how design elements from the UI Quality Constitution fit. I'm excited about the custom hero visual.\n\n\n**Refining UI Component Design**\n\nI'm now iterating on the design for `/admin/clients/[id]/page.tsx`, envisioning a premium, interactive client detail page. I'm focusing on incorporating an SVG/CSS architectural graphic, possibly a map of an HSM Enclave Boundary, or an eBPF Kernel Security ring! I'm also planning a narrative timeline for key verification and attestation checkpoints. I like the idea of a Bento grid or clean card layout with tabbed content. I'm also exploring subtle animated background or grid effects. I've found an opportunity to level up the side drawer from `app/admin/clients/page.tsx`, and I'm ready to add a \"View Deep Audit Record\" button or link. I see I can use `lucide-react`'s `ArrowLeft`, `Users`, `ShieldCheck`, and `Cpu`. I will add a button and route to the deep audit record.\n\n\n**Adding Deep Audit Link**\n\nI'm now checking if I can import `ShieldCheck` in `app/admin/clients/page.tsx`, and I see I already have related icons imported. I'm ready to add a \"Deep Audit Panel\" button. It will use a blue color scheme, and include the `ShieldCheck` icon, creating a direct link to the detailed audit page.\n\n\n**Refining Icon Choice**\n\nI'm now deciding between `Shield`, `ArrowLeft`, and `ShieldCheck` icons for the \"Deep Audit Panel\" button. I'm reviewing the drawer footer in `app/admin/clients/page.tsx` for visual integration. I think I'll look at incorporating the `ShieldCheck` icon, aligning with the existing UI style.\n\n\n**Implementing Deep Audit Button**\n\nI'm now integrating a \"Open Deep Audit Record\" button into the client detail drawer. I've decided to add it as a new full-width button. I've confirmed `Layers` is imported and am preparing the code insertion within `app/admin/clients/page.tsx` for a clean implementation. I will check for where the `selectedClient` drawer footer is in `app/admin/clients/page.tsx` to insert it cleanly.\n\n\n**Locating Insertion Point**\n\nI've located the likely insertion point for the deep audit button within `app/admin/clients/page.tsx`, around line 911-936. I'm focusing on the drawer footer actions to implement the new full-width button. I'll insert it there, to keep UI consistency.\n\n\n\n**Structuring Button Actions**\n\nI'm now determining the optimal placement for the \"Open Deep Audit Record\" button in the client detail drawer. I've decided it's best positioned as a secondary CTA, right after the \"Establish Portal Mirror Handshake\" button. I will add it as a new full-width button, and position the existing \"Assign Owner\" and \"Close Ledger\" actions as tertiary, half-width CTAs. This creates a clear hierarchy of actions.\n\n\n\n**Enriching Detail Page**\n\nI'm now diving into the enhancement of `app/admin/clients/[id]/page.tsx`. I'm going to start by pulling the `clientId` from params. Then, I'll attempt to find the client details from `previewClientAccounts`, falling back to a mock enriched object if needed. My focus is on crafting a visually engaging, high-level client audit page. I am considering a Hero Status Panel, a dynamic HSM Enclave Map, and a continuous audit Narrative Timeline Checklist.\n\n\n**Designing Detail Page Elements**\n\nI'm now deep in the design for the enhanced detail page. I'm focusing on the architectural components, starting with a Secure Handshake Status, a Kernel Boundary Verification, and Guardrail Compliance section. I will also incorporate an Attestation Ledger status, a live projects and multi-agent lattice overview, a bento grid of system metrics, and an interactive console for cold re-attestation and HSM seal rotation. Finally, I'm checking for console logs or unresolved imports, and I'll use the editor tool to add the deep audit button to the page.\n\n\n\n"}}
