ode block, looking at nested elements and their attributes. I suspect the issue lies within the character count inflation occurring when rendering the conditional and associated SVG. My scrutiny involves analyzing inline styles, especially those with potential for hidden characters or improper encoding, as well as the path data within the SVG element. I'm testing the effect of separating all the components and formatting into individual HTML pages.\n\n\n**Isolating SVG Inflation**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on a particular SVG element, specifically the path data, that appears to be inflating the character count. My focus is the `d` attribute within the SVG, as well as the text rendering. I am systematically checking the inline styling and its contribution to inflated totals. It appears removing the SVG reduces counts to a new lower total. I'm now going to explore different encoding formats.\n\n\n"}}
